# CB-3.6 — Systemd preset for Mackes Desktop Environment (MDE) 2.0.0.
#
# Fedora's systemd-preset mechanism reads files under
# /usr/lib/systemd/user-preset/ in lexical order to decide whether a
# unit is enabled by default for new users. `enable` here means
# "enable this user unit on first encounter unless the user has
# explicitly disabled it." Existing installs are unaffected — preset
# only governs first-time enable decisions.
#
# v2.0.0 — Phase B.13 retired 10 standalone systemd units that the
# v1.x preset enabled (clipboard, mdns, fs_sync, media_sync,
# remmina_sync, ansible_pull, kdc_bridge, heartbeat,
# notification_relay, notifications_server); their workers now run
# inside `mded serve` (the unified meta-daemon). The preset shrinks
# accordingly.
#
# What's left to enable at first encounter:
#
#   * mde-session.service — user-session orchestrator (sway +
#     autostarted Iced panel + Iced applets + Iced workbench +
#     mde-files). Replaces the v1.x `mackes-enforce-session`
#     autostart shim entirely.

enable mde-session.service
